/-!
# Chapter VII, Section 1: outline

This section of the source is a roadmap for the proof of global class field
theory.  It introduces no numbered mathematical assertion: it explains how
the cohomology of ideles, Herbrand quotients, the two inequalities, and the
global fundamental class will be combined to prove the reciprocity and
existence theorems.

The quotient-group form of the finite reciprocity law described here is
already recorded in `GlobalReciprocity.Recip`.  The following sections
formalize the ingredients of the proof as far as the current cohomology and
idele APIs permit.
-/
